  "text": "Proposition 3 (Kolchin-Kovacic, [CITATION_1] prop 1.31 & cor 1.32). Let k be a C 1 field. Consider a differential system Y ′ = AY with A ∈ Mat(n,k). Assume that the differential Galois group G (over k) is connected and let g be its Lie algebra. Let H ⊂ GL n (C) be a connected algebraic group whose Lie algebra h satisfies A ∈ h(k). Then:",
